This paper is about a spoken dialogue system, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of statistical dialogue management and the focus on reducing data needs suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of machine learning techniques and the focus on performance evaluation suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The user study and focus on user experience suggest that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SD (Sound) may also be relevant categories.
